  "body": "## Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n1) Author a message with a code block. For example:\r\n\r\n  --- Status message: ---\r\n\r\n  Here is a code block:\r\n\r\n  \\```\r\n  proc main = \r\n  &nbsp; &nbsp; echo \"hello world\"\r\n  \\```\r\n\r\n--- Status message end ---\r\n\r\n2) Click \"Edit\" on the message\r\n\r\n3) Notice how the code block is flattened not a single line, not containing any of the backtick characters.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nI expect the Edit operation to allow me to tweak the original input text of the message, containing the backtick characters exactly as I entered them before sending it in step 1). This makes it easy to introduce small tweaks to the message.\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\nStatus Desktop 0.8 on macOS\r\n",
